    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-12-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-12-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="204"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Morris</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 100.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-12-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 18, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: For your information, I enclose herewith a
                    transcript of an instruction of the 14th instant,<note n="*" xml:id="d204fn1"
                        >For enclosure see correspondence with the consul general of the United
                        States at Alexandria, Egypt.</note> addressed to the consul general of the
                    United States at Alexandria, upon the subject of the apprehended renewal of the
                    expedition from that place of Nubian negroes to be engaged on the part of France
                    in the war waged between that country and Mexico. A copy of the assurance of Mr.
                    Drouyn de Lhuys, to which reference is made therein, is also herewith
                    enclosed.</p>
                <p>Should circumstances require it, you will communicate a copy of the instruction
                    to Mr. Hale to the Sultan’s government.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">E. Joy Morris,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
